trivial -- when you have such a small amount of code for the payload, you can inline it:
onSuccess.accept(InterpretResult.builder()
    .sentiment(sentiment)
    .build());

Actually, you could probably even bring that whole thing up into the try block:
try {
    onSuccess.accept(InterpretResult.builder()
        .sentiment(fetchSentiment(text))
        .build());
} catch (PredictionsException sentimentDetectionFailure) {
    onError.accept(sentimentDetectionFailure);
}

