timeline.bodyText:
You have a number of different components that have a similar lifecycle: load(), isLoaded().
You could make a Loadable interface:
// V = value type for thing that is loaded, e.g. a Map<String, Integer> dictionary, etc.
interface Loadable<V> {
    void load();
    void unload();
    boolean isLoaded();
    onLoaded(Consumer<V> valueConsumer);
    onUnloaded(Action unloadAction);
    @Nullable V value()
}

If you have somehting like this, you can externalize all of these details into small little template files and compartmentalize the load/validation logic into them.
Then the classification refers to them more like:
for (Loadable<?> dependency : LOADABLES) {
    if (!dependency.isLoaded()) {
        dependency.load();
    }
}

I guess you'd want this to happen as a down-stream result of the call-chain from thePlugin<?>'s initialize() lifecycle method.

